            <div class=\"header-date\">March 1, 2026</div>\n   262→        </div>\n   263→    </header>\n   264→\n   265→    <div class=\"subtitle\">\n   266→        <div class=\"subtitle-text\">\n   267→            Daily intelligence on AI coding agents, developer tools, and the future of software engineering\n   268→        </div>\n   269→    </div>\n   270→\n   271→    <main>\n   272→        <div class=\"three-column-layout\">\n   273→            <!-- New Products Section -->\n   274→            <section class=\"new-products\">\n   275→                <div class=\"section-header\">New Products</div>\n   276→                <div class=\"section-content\">\n   277→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   278→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   279→                            <a href=\"https://github.com/openclaw\" class=\"accent-link\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw v2026.2.17</a>\n   280→                        </div>\n   281→                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n   282→                            Open-source local-first AI agent platform for coding and task automation. Features workspace memory system, multi-platform support (macOS/Windows/Linux/mobile), and integrates with chat platforms. Version 2026.2.17 added Sonnet 4.6, 1M context testing, sub-agent generation from chats, and iOS share extensions.\n   283→                        </div>\n   284→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   285→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI coding agent</span>\n   286→                            <span class=\"source-tag\">GitHub</span>\n   287→                            <span class=\"source-tag\">TechCrunch</span>\n   288→                            <span class=\"source-tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   289→                        </div>\n   290→                        <div class=\"community-quote\">\n   291→                            \"Phenomenal open-source success in the AI agent space. Over 196,000 GitHub stars by late February 2026. Local-first architecture ensures data privacy - no cloud uploads. Over 300 derivative projects have emerged on GitHub.\"\n   292→                        </div>\n   293→                    </div>\n   294→                </div>\n   295→            </section>\n   296→\n   297→            <!-- Whitelist Updates Section -->\n   298→            <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n   299→                <div class=\"section-header\">Whitelist Updates</div>\n   300→                <div class=\"section-content\">\n   301→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   302→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   303→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">Claude Code</span>\n   304→                            <a href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/blog\" class=\"accent-link\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Sonnet 4.6 Model Release</a>\n   305→                        </div>\n   306→                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n   307→                            <span class=\"update-type\">Release</span>\n   308→                            Anthropic released Claude Sonnet 4.6 on February 17, 2026, delivering Opus-level performance at Sonnet-level pricing. Features 1M token context window, ~75-79.6% SWE-bench score, 72.5% OSWorld score, and enhanced capabilities in coding, agent tasks, computer use, and long-context reasoning.\n   309→                        </div>\n   310→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">2026-02-17</div>\n   311→                        <div class=\"community-quote feedback-positive\">\n   312→                            \"70% of developers preferred Sonnet 4.6 over Sonnet 4.5; 59% preferred it over flagship Opus 4.5\"\n   313→                        </div>\n   314→                        <div class=\"community-quote feedback-positive\">\n   315→                            \"1 million tokens? Finally found a model that can read my entire messy codebase without judging it\"\n   316→                        </div>\n   317→                    </div>\n   318→\n   319→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   320→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   321→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">Codex CLI</span>\n   322→                            <a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" class=\"accent-link\" target=\"_blank\">Comprehensive Overhaul</a>\n   323→                        </div>\n   324→                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n   325→                            <span class=\"update-type\">Feature</span>\n   326→                            OpenAI released major Codex updates on February 9, 2026: New GPT-5.2-Codex model with 40% faster reasoning, 400K token input capacity, support for 50+ programming languages, multi-agent parallel execution, and new macOS desktop application.\n   327→                        </div>\n   328→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">2026-02-09</div>\n   329→                        <div class=\"community-quote feedback-negative\">\n   330→                            \"Complex configuration requirements and output stability issues\"\n   331→                        </div>\n   332→                        <div class=\"community-quote feedback-negative\">\n   333→                            \"Mac performance overhead concerns\"\n   334→                        </div>\n   335→                    </div>\n   336→\n   337→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   338→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   339→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">Cursor</span>\n   340→                            <a href=\"https://cursor.sh\" class=\"accent-link\" target=\"_blank\">Composer 1.5 Model Release</a>\n   341→                        </div>\n   342→                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n   343→                            <span class=\"update-type\">Release</span>\n   344→                            Cursor released Composer 1.5 on February 9, 2026, a self-developed AI programming model 4x faster than equivalents with 20x increased reinforcement learning training scale. Specialized for multi-file editing with project-level understanding.\n   345→                        </div>\n   346→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">2026-02-09</div>\n   347→                        <div class=\"community-quote feedback-neutral\">\n   348→                            \"Sitting there watching 8 AI agents race, you can smell the tokens burning furiously\"\n   349→                        </div>\n   350→                        <div class=\"community-quote feedback-positive\">\n   351→                            \"Revolutionary parallel processing (up to 8 Agents)\"\n   352→                        </div>\n   353→                    </div>\n   354→\n   355→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   356→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   357→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">Gemini CLI</span>\n   358→                            <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\" class=\"accent-link\" target=\"_blank\">v0.26.0 Release</a>\n   359→                        </div>\n   360→                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n   361→                            <span class=\"update-type\">Release</span>\n   362→                            Version 0.26.0 released around February 1, 2026. Building on v0.22.0 (January 2026) which opened Gemini 3 series models to free users, includes Conductor extension for active project management, Endor Labs security integration, and audio/video processing capabilities.\n   363→                        </div>\n   364→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">2026-02-01</div>\n   365→                    </div>\n   366→                </div>\n   367→            </section>\n   368→\n   369→            <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n   370→            <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n   371→                <div class=\"section-header\">Technical Insights</div>\n   372→                <div class=\"section-content\">\n   373→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   374→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   375→                            <a href=\"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A06NX300\" class=\"accent-link\" target=\"_blank\">Stanford CS146S: The Modern Software Developer Course Launch</a>\n   376→                        </div>\n   377→                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n   378→                            Stanford released a comprehensive course focusing on AI-assisted development, reflecting how LLM Agent capabilities (especially Claude and Codex) crossed a coherence threshold in late 2025, causing a phase change in software engineering. The course emphasizes \"Vibe Coding\" methodologies.\n   379→                        </div>\n   380→                        <div class=\"insight-author\">\n   381→                            <span class=\"source-tag\">Stanford University</span>\n   382→                            <span class=\"source-tag\">discussed by Simon Willison</span>\n   383→                        </div>\n   384→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">2026-02-24</div>\n   385→                        <div>\n   386→                            <span class=\"topic-tag\">AI education</span>\n   387→                            <span class=\"topic-tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n   388→                            <span class=\"topic-tag\">LLM agents</span>\n   389→                        </div>\n   390→                    </div>\n   391→                </div>\n   392→            </section>\n   393→        </div>\n   394→    </main>\n   395→\n   396→    <footer>\n   397→        <a href=\"#\">Archive</a>\n   398→        <a href=\"#\">About</a>\n   399→        <a href=\"#\">Subscribe</a>\n   400→        <a href=\"#\">GitHub</a>\n   401→        <div style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">\